<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-010-257 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 504 612</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Nov 18 1991 v13 n46 p113(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>QuickC is a one-stop development tool: Windows integratedenvironment spares tedious module switching. (Software Review)(Microsoft QuickC for Windows) (Evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Forer, Douglas; Peterley, Nicholas.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft Corp's QuickC for Windows is an integrated developmentenvironment based on the C language that lets users move easilybetween editing, prototyping and debugging modules by running themin different windows.andP;  The editor lets users edit up to 16 sourcefiles at one time; the Image and Dialog Editor tools resemblethose in the Windows Software Development Kit.andP;  Performanceratings are excellent for both the programming environment andlanguage extensions.andP;  Debugging is rated very good.andP;  Documentationis very good, as is ease of use.andP;  The integrated graphical userinterface simplifies virtually every programming task.andP;  Errorhandling is very good.andP;  Microsoft provides an Errors window thatis automatically brought to the foreground when errors occurduring compiling or linking.andP;  Support policies are good, andtechnical support is very good.andP;  QuickC for Windows is anexcellent value at $199.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   QuickC for Windows (Program development software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     Program development softwareEvaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>